						<note><p>1921–?</p><p>Later name Shlomo Schmiedt. Before the war he lived in Prague. In 1942 he was deported to the
								Theresienstadt (Terezín) ghetto, from which he was sent in autumn 1944 to Auschwitz-Birkenau. After the war he was one
								of the important co-workers of the Documentation campaign (Dokumentační akce). Later Schmiedt emigrated to
							Israel.</p></note>
					</person>
					<person xml:id="ehri_et_shek_zeev">
						<persName>Shek, Zeev</persName>
						<note><p>1920–1978</p><p>Born in Olomouc. Active in the Zionist movement, member of Maccabi Hatzair. In 1943 he was deported
								to the Theresienstadt (Terezín) ghetto, where he became one of the Hechalutz leaders. In autumn 1944 he was
								transported to Auschwitz-Birkenau. After the war he became one of the main initiator of the Documentation campaign
								(Dokumentační akce). In 1946 he emigrated to Palestine, where he worked for the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and in the
								diplomatic services. In 1967 Sheck was appointed as the Israeli Ambassador in Vienna. In 1977 he was sent to serve as
								the Israeli Ambassador in Rome, where he has died one year later.</p></note>
					</person>
