	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1" facs="EHRI-ET-JMP006_01.jpg"/>

			<p>Passage from a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-716" type="subject">letter</term></p>

			<p>to Mr. <persName ref="#ehri_et_glaser_hugo">Hugo Glaser</persName>, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html"
					>Prague</placeName> XII., <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Zelená 7</placeName>, from Mr. <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_burg_berthold">Berthold Burg</persName>, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650"
					type="subject">prisoner</term> of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject"
					>concentration camps</term> in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-513">Lodz</placeName>,
					<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-1444" type="camp">Poznan</placeName>, <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2">Auschwitz</placeName> and <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-15" type="camp">Fürstengrube</placeName>, current profession interpreter
				with Co.C 823 T.D.Bn. A.P.O. 339, <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004289" type="subject"
					>U.S.Army</orgName> c/o Postmaster N.Y.</p>

			<p>Dear <persName ref="#ehri_et_glaser_hugo">Glasers</persName>,</p>
			<p>I have just received a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-716" type="subject">letter</term>
				from Napoleon and I am as happy as a child to hear that you are healthy and home once again. In <date when="1944-10">October</date>
				last year, I learned that you were in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-449" type="ghetto"
					>Theresienstadt</placeName> and that you were doing well, that little <persName ref="#ehri_et_glaser_hugo">Hugo</persName> was
				working in a bakery, and that after 9 years – instead of after 9 months – you had a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">boy</term>. Where, pray, is this <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">child</term>?</p>

			<p>My mother was <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-499" type="subject">gassed</term>.</p>

			<p>I have some sad news for you, but you have seen so much that we need not hesitate, especially when it concerns our dearest loved
				ones.</p>

			<p>This is what happened: on <date when="1943-12-18">December 18th, 1943</date>, when we were in the <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-15" type="camp">Fürstengrube </placeName><term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term> near <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2">Auschwitz</placeName>, around midnight, the afternoon shift returned to
				the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term>. I was in <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-491" type="subject">KB</term> at the time. After being injured in the
				mine, I had a bad hemorrhage in my ankle and whatnot. <persName ref="#ehri_et_glaser_max">Max</persName> was a <foreign xml:lang="de"
					>Vorarbeiter</foreign> on the afternoon shift.</p>

			<p>Two days earlier, <distinct type="camp_language">zugangi</distinct> arrived in the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term> – <placeName ref="#ehri_et_galicia"
					>Galicians</placeName> – Jews from <placeName ref="#ehri_et_galicia">Galicia</placeName>. Some lived nearby, on the border of
				Upper <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3066138/silesia.html">Silesia</placeName> and <placeName ref="#ehri_et_galicia"
					>Galicia</placeName>. One of them <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escaped</term>
				at the start of his shift. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term> was
				celebrating <foreign xml:lang="de">Julfest</foreign> that day. When the shift returned to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-294" type="subject">Lagerführer</term>- <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-294" type="subject">Hauptscharführer</term>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_moll_otto">Moll</persName> (I remember his name, he’s one of the biggest murderers in all of <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2">Auschwitz</placeName>, <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2">Birkenau</placeName> and their surroundings) was drunk when he let them
				in. He <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-634" type="subject">interrogated</term> the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-485" type="subject">capo</term> and then <foreign xml:lang="de"
					>Vorarbeiter</foreign>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">Häftling</term> to find out who had <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escaped</term>, and, unfortunately, that <foreign
					xml:lang="de">Vorarbeiter</foreign> was <persName ref="#ehri_et_glaser_max">Max</persName>. <persName ref="#ehri_et_glaser_max"
					>Max</persName> thought that he could explain everything to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-294" type="subject">Lagerführer</term> and calm him down,
				but he miscalculated. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-294" type="subject"
					>Lagerführer</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">shot</term> him and 5 or 6 other <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">Häftlings</term>. He would have shot more if <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_schmidt_max">Max Schmidt</persName>, his deputy at the time, hadn’t stopped him. Later, <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_schmidt_max">Max Schmidt</persName> became our <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-294" type="subject">Lagerführer</term>.</p>

			<p>I became a <distinct type="camp_language">Rapportschreiber</distinct> in <date when="1944-12">December 1944</date>, and I discovered a
				statement with the following contents:</p>

			<p>On <date when="1944-12-08">8. 12. 1944</date> the afternoon shift returned to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term> at the usual hour during an air raid
				siren. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">Häftling</term>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_glaser_max">Max Glaser</persName>, a <term type="subject" ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_czechs">Czech</term>
				Jew, suddenly attacked an <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS-man</term>, using the
				cover of a total <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-624" type="subject">blackout</term>, and
				tried to grab his service pistol. But the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject"
					>SS-man</term> managed to defend himself, discharged his weapon, and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">killed</term> him. Several <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">häftlings</term> used the confusion to attempt a mass
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escape</term> – <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject"><foreign xml:lang="de"
				>Massenausbruch</foreign></term>. The guards immediately opened fire on them, and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">shot</term> another 5 or 6; one <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escaped</term>. This was followed by signatures.</p>

			<p>Maybe you have heard about this already. These are the facts I’ve received from eyewitnesses.</p>

			<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-657" type="subject">Documentary campaign</term>:</p>
			<p>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_schmiedt_alexander">Alex. Schmiedt</persName>
			</p>
			<p>
				<date when="1945-09-12">12.9.1945</date>
			</p>
			<p>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_shek_zeev">Scheck</persName>
			</p>
